Project:  REST-API-for-Remote-Labs-Server
Framework: Node.JS
Copyright: 2011 Centre for Educational Innovation and Technology
----------------------------------------------------------------

Instructions
------------

1. Install Node.JS

2. Install and setup MySQL

3. Use database dump file (Database Construction) to create and populate tables

4. In store-mysql.js must enter appropriate database access details

5. Configure and create bindings for node-mysql-libmysqlclient module (https://github.com/Sannis/node-mysql-libmysqlclient). Take note of dependencies and please use the module included in the project as new version has remote some functions which this project depends on (i.e. Fetch).

6. Run restserver.js script to start the server
